## Implementation Details

The implementation follows the official Vercel documentation exactly:

```typescript
import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next"

export default function RootLayout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return (
    <html lang="en">
      <body>
        {children}
        <Analytics />
      </body>
    </html>
  )
}
```

This placement ensures that analytics tracking is active on all pages of the application.

## Next Steps for User

To complete the setup and start receiving analytics data:

1. **Enable Analytics in Vercel Dashboard**:
   - Navigate to your project on Vercel
   - Go to the Analytics tab
   - Click the "Enable" button
   - This activates the `/_vercel/insights/*` routes

2. **Deploy to Vercel**:
   - Run `vercel deploy` or push to your connected Git repository
   - Analytics will automatically begin tracking after deployment

3. **Verify Analytics is Working**:
   - Visit your deployed site
   - Open browser DevTools > Network tab
   - Look for requests to `/_vercel/insights/view`
   - Check your Vercel dashboard Analytics section for data

